# Physics & Movement System

Read `docs/Physics_Movement_Spec.md` before making any changes.

## Core Design Decisions
- Ships use `CharacterBody2D` with **manual velocity** — NOT `RigidBody2D`
- Angular inertia via `max_angular_accel` — heavier ships turn slower
- Assisted steering: auto counter-torque prevents overshoot (no nav computer module at MVP)
- Shared thruster budget: turning takes priority, strafing gets the remainder
- Partial alignment drag: only lateral velocity bleeds on hard turns (not forward momentum)
- Projectiles inherit firing ship's velocity at spawn

## PerformanceMonitor Metrics (use exactly these strings)
- `Physics.move_and_slide` — wrap the move_and_slide call
- `Physics.thruster_allocation` — wrap the thruster budget calculation
- `Physics.active_bodies` — set_count each frame

## Key Classes
- `SpaceBody.gd` — base class for anything with physics (ships, asteroids)
- `Ship.gd` — extends SpaceBody, adds ship-specific systems

## Watch Out For
- Don't call `move_and_slide()` more than once per frame per body
- Thruster budget is a shared resource — turning always wins, document why
- Drag should only affect the lateral component during hard turns, not all velocity
- All mass/thrust/drag values come from JSON, never hardcode them
